description:
Rare (not really) and exclusive (liar) early demo from The October Theory – check the review below

	The October Theory – It All Starts At One (demo)
This three track demo certainly shows some promise for Sheffield lads The October Theory – opener “Detached By Dial TOne” is a no nonsense screamcore track whilst “The Afterlife Party” has puncier, almost punk guitars.  There’s definatly the base for a good band here, the only main flaw being the clean sung vocals which are mostly off key and spoil what are otherwise good bare knuckle metallic rock songs.
(Rhodsey)
